text.tspan: Human Development Index vs. GDP per capita, 1990 to 2023
The Human Development Index (HDI) is a summary measure of key dimensions of human development: a long
and healthy life, a good education, and a decent standard of living. GDP per capita is adjusted for inflation and
differences in living costs between countries.
GDP per capita (international-$ in 2021 prices; plotted on a logarithmic axis)
Data source: UNDP, Human Development Report (2025); Eurostat, OECD, IMF, and World Bank (2025)
